==English==

===Alternate spelling===
*corner stone

===Noun===
'''cornerstone'''

# A [[stone]] that forms the [[base]] of a [[corner]] of a building, joining two walls.
#:Quotation:  A prince who regarded uniformity of faith as the '''corner stone''' of his government. --Prescott
# A vital part or basis.
#:Example:  Sugar was the '''cornerstone''' of the country's economy.

